@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "8. Article ";
}

<div class="container">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <p>The <code>&lt;article&gt;</code> element is used to identify a section of independent, self-contained content that may be independently distributed or reused. We'll often use the <code>&lt;article&gt;</code> element to mark up blog posts, newspaper articles, user-submitted content, and the like.</p>

    <p>When deciding whether to use the <code>&lt;article&gt;</code> element, we must determine if the content within the element could be replicated elsewhere without any confusion. If the content within the <code>&lt;article&gt;</code> element were removed from the context of the page and placed, for example, within an email or printed work, that content should still make sense.</p>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">HTML Example</div>
        <div class="code-content">
<pre><code class="language-html">
&lt;article&gt;
  &lt;h2&gt;The Rise of Web Development&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Web development has evolved rapidly over the past decade, introducing new technologies and best practices that have revolutionized how we build websites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/article&gt;
</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="navigation-buttons">
        <a href="@Url.Action("NavElement", "Frontend")" class="btn btn-outline-primary">← Navigation Element</a>
        <a href="@Url.Action("SectionElement", "Frontend")" class="btn btn-primary">Section Element →</a>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .container {
        max-width: 850px;
        padding: 20px;
        background-color: var(--bs-body-bg);
    }

    h1 {
        color: var(--bs-heading-color);
        margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    p {
        color: var(--bs-body-color);
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    code {
        font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;
        background-color: #eef;
        padding: 2px 5px;
        border-radius: 4px;
    }

    .code-container {
        margin: 25px 0;
        border: 1px solid var(--bs-border-color);
        border-radius: 5px;
        background-color: #f9f9f9;
        overflow-x: auto;
    }

    .code-header {
        background-color: #e9ecef;
        padding: 10px 15px;
        font-family: monospace;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: #333;
    }

    .code-content {
        padding: 15px;
    }

    .navigation-buttons {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        margin-top: 30px;
    }

    .btn {
        padding: 8px 20px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        font-weight: 500;
    }

    .btn-primary {
        background-color: var(--bs-primary);
        border-color: var(--bs-primary);
    }

    .btn-outline-primary {
        color: var(--bs-primary);
        border-color: var(--bs-primary);
    }
</style>
